text: Whelan is an unincorporated community in Whitman County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Whelan was established in 1890, and remained in operation until 1895. The community was named after a railroad official. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Whitman County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Whelan, Washington
